default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGatwick North Termi
defaultnal does not appear to have any reliable passenger information system. It 
defaultsh
defaultould have been
default possible
default to have provided information about the situation and its cause using 
defaultflipcharts
default, whiteboards or blackboards
default.
default No-one bothered to 
defaultwarn passengers 
defaultin the secur
defaultity area 
defaultabout the situation they would find in the departure lounge. No-one bothered to explain to
default passengers the nature or scope of the problems faced or how it was planned to deal with the problems.
default&#xa0;
defaultvi)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBritish Airways
default 
defaultshould have had identifiable staff p
defaultresent. The absence of BA staff was interpreted by many passengers as a lack of concern for customers, complacency and even contempt. At no time was any reliable information or advice beyond the limited information on the departures screen given to any pas
defaultsenger. There was no indication - at any time - that the situation was being managed. No explanation was given about delayed departures, the reasons for delays or plans to overcome identified problems
default.
