defaultRecommendationsdefault&#xa0;defaulti)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGatwick
default Airport, toge
defaultther with carriers operating there, should install information systems which can provide 
defaultreliable 
defaultexplanatory, 
defaultnarrative
default and detailed
default information to passengers, not just details of arrival and departure.
default&#xa0;
defaultii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhen public address announcements are made, there s
defaulthould be a mechanism for routine security recorded announcements to be sup
defaultp
defaultressed
default when operational and passenger service announcements are being made.
default&#xa0;
defaultiii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhere it is necessary to provide specific information to specific groups of passengers, the opportunity 
defaultshould be taken to segregate such passengers from others in the departure lounge.
default&#xa0;
defaultiv)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere should always be representatives of carriers available to provide information and deal with enquiries.
default&#xa0;
defaultv)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAppropriate information about operational problems which may af
defaultfect passengers should be available in the check-in area and the security check area.
